<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_SnowyEscape_RockClimbing" s="254295">
  <T n="category">254282<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SnowyEscape--></T>
  <T n="name">0x84C66E27<!--String: "Rock Climbing"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP10\UI\Lessons\EP10_RockClimbing_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8803dbf88756d5ca</T>
      <T n="text">0x945CAF66<!--String: "Time to raise your expectations of what an outdoor activity can be. Rock Climbing is a great way for your Sims to exercise, replenish fun, and eventually scale Mt. Komorebi on a mountain excursion."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP10\UI\Lessons\EP10_RockClimbing_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8803dbf88756d5c9</T>
      <T n="text">0x84FDDD87<!--String: "You can pick up the rock climbing skill by purchasing skill books, researching handhold techniques on a computer, or by getting out into the world and trying to climb a wall. Sims starting out will be limited to the small training wall located near the base of the Bunny Slopes in the Yukimatsu neighborhood. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP10\UI\Lessons\EP10_RockClimbing_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8803dbf88756d5c8</T>
      <T n="text">0xF617148C<!--String: "The small rock wall for beginners is in the <b>Yukimatsu neighborhood</b> at the base of the Bunny Slope.\n\nMedium rock walls for more capable climbers are found in the bamboo forest in the <b>Senbamachi neighborhood</b>, and on the climb up Mt. Komorebi. Look for your first icy wall at the top of the gondola.\n\nThe tallest rock wall, only for the most skilled sims, is located in the Croft Icefall on your way up Mt. Komorebi. Sims will encounter this on a <b>Mountain Excursion</b>"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP10\UI\Lessons\EP10_RockClimbing_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8803dbf88756d5cf</T>
      <T n="text">0x886BE879<!--String: "Besides raising skill, there are multiple ways for a Sim to improve their success climbing a rock wall.\n\nThe first is to purchase climbing gear from the computer. Make sure to equip the gear from the Sim's inventory before starting the climb."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP10\UI\Lessons\EP10_RockClimbing_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8803dbf88756d5ce</T>
      <T n="text">0x932ED014<!--String: "Your Sim can also use the chalk hands and do pre-climb stretch interactions before a climb. These will both provide buffs that get your Sim ready for the accent. It may mean the difference between reaching the top and falling to their death."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP10\UI\Lessons\EP10_RockClimbing_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:8803dbf88756d5cd</T>
      <T n="text">0x13DC8C56<!--String: "<b>Death</b> is a possibility when climbing on the tallest rock wall located in The Croft Icefall as you accent Mt. Komorebi. Be very careful on this wall. If your sim is already battered and bruised from previous falls, they may want to rest a bit longer before trying this climb."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
</I>